text:
ik zou trouwens ook met de #metoo - actie kunnen meedoen, maar wie gelooft nu mijn verhaal, voor iedereen is het waarschijnlijk het gedacht van "jaja ineens heeft ze zo een trauma, waarschijnlijk omdat iedereen dat heeft.". maar goed:

ik volgde mijn lager onderwijs in het buitengewoon onderwijs. het was in het tweede leerjaar. dat er een periode was dat iedere "speeltijd" twee jongens van mijn klas, zich iedere keer naar mij wende. of wel werd ik tegen de muur geduwd, of wel was het de vloer. ze duwden/legden zich heel hard tegen mij Ã©n maakte schuivende bewegingen op mij (een tekening op wat het moest lijken, daar dien ik geen tekening voor te moeten maken.). en zo een hele periode lang, natuurlijk deed het wat met mij. ik had het lang verzwegen, omdat ik bang was het te melden. tot ik het eens tegen mijn moeder vertelde, en zij via mijn schoolagenda, mijn toenmalige leerkracht op de hoogte bracht. na een tijdje hield het op.

nu ik merk in relaties, of gewoon in het algemeen, dat ik een ongemakkelijk gevoel in me krijg, een niet prettig gevoel. en ik geloof dat het door dit trauma komt. niemand van de mensen die nu in mijn leven zijn weten dit niet...

text:
itâ€™s truly disturbing the entitlement that society feels they have to disrespect women. it is in-fact a cultural tradition to treat women as inanimate objects to intrude upon sexually. it is also a social norm for black women especially to not have any governance over their own bodies and to be labeled as intolerable when they have any convictions against people over stepping personal boundaries that cause them pain, discomfort, or disease. 
to the extent that we are allowed to die during childbirth. when performing mundane task we can be subject to unwanted sexual advances at any given time. somehow it will always be something that we did. furthermore our convictions against sexual violence be it verbally or physically will always prove to be more problematic than the assaulting actions or words cast against us. thatâ€™s fine, but for those who think that way i insist for those people to redirect themselves out of my path completely. i do not wish to deal with it, i should not have to deal with it, and i will not deal with it.

regards,
us

text:
tuesday, november 27th at the university of minnesota, in concert with a panel of nonprofit leaders from around the twin cities, the kelly nicole foundation proudly presents an unforgettable evening of music, film and inspiration.  join us for an artistic exploration of overcoming shame featuring music by the late artist, kelly nicole and the award-winning documentary on her battle with a trauma-based eating disorder.  inspired by the lyric "it's all my fault, but i'm not to blame," the panel will take audience questions, so we want to hear from you.  bring a friend and join the conversation.  free food, great music and film.  walter library 402, november 27th at 5:30pm.  visit kellynicole.com for more information on the music behind the mission.  admission will be free.  survivors will be heard.

#amplified #kellynicolefoundation #hatebecoming #ptsd #trauma #metoo #edrecovery #eatingdisorderawareness #music #film #art #mentalhealth #umn #universityofminnesota #eatingdisorder

text:
a loving weekend gone horribly wrong. the details still impossible for me to put into words.
.
all i can say is that one year ago, the mask fell. fully and onto the floor. what was said and done was unforgivable. i had come face-to-face with the narcissist, the alcoholic, and the monster before. but this time i met the sociopath.
.
as traumatic as it was, i suppose it needed to happen. because one year ago i finally got scared off. i finally had enough.
.
today i am celebrating choosing better. choosing respect over selfishness, truth over ignorance, good over evil, integrity over dishonesty, authenticity over the disingenuous, and most importantly, choosing real love over fake love in disguise. choosing real, warm, genuine, honest, healthy love over unbalanced, abusive, toxic relationships where i am merely narcissistic supply. ğŸ™ŒğŸ¼ğŸ™ŒğŸ¼ğŸ™ŒğŸ¼ğŸ’›ğŸ¦‹

text:
the first ten lies they tell you in high school 
1. we are here to help you. 
2. you will have time to get to your class before the bell rings. 
3. the dress code will be enforced. 
4. no smoking is allowed on school grounds. 
5. our football team will win the championship this year. 
6. we expect more of you here. 
7. guidance counselors are always available to listen. 
8. your schedule was created with you in mind. 
9. your locker combination is private. 
10. these will be the years you look back on fondly. ğŸŒ²
while devouring many ya options in the late 90s/early 00s, i never actually read speak by laurie halse anderson. better late than never because i loved every page of this book. if anyone has been struggling to articulate their feelings of rage or anguish in light of the recent kavanaugh/blasey ford hearing, i strongly suggest giving this a first time read, or even a revisit. believe women.

text:
i am utterly outraged by this story. 
i have read several articles just because i really struggle to believe that in 2018 this has been allowed to happen. in. a. court. room!

i tend to shy away from serious issues because i firmly believe that everyone has their own opinion and i donâ€™t feel the need to force mine on anyone.  however, bullying and injustice make me feel rage in my gut.  i feel like both have occurred in this circumstance.  the humiliation this poor girl faced being forced to hold up her underwear during the trial is disgusting. 
i have tried to get my head round this story since i read it and have cried many quiet tears of frustration and anger, now, i am about to publicly share something that only a handful of people know. 
i was raped. 
i did not report it and iâ€™ll tell you why;

i knew what happened, i knew i said â€œnoâ€ very clearly.  i knew i was laughed at. 
nothing could make it â€˜not have happenedâ€™. reporting what happened would have led to a lot of questioning, rightly so, i imagine being falsely accused of rape is equally life shattering.  however, i didnâ€™t feel strong enough to go through that, to have what i knew happened gone over and over.  i wanted to pretend it hadnâ€™t happened. 
i also felt that for me, denial and self preservation was what would get me through.  it did. even if everyone did know what happened and he was punished, i would still be as broken as i was except the difference would be that everyone would know how broken i was.  i didnâ€™t want that for me or for my family.  worst case scenario for me was that i might be branded a liar and he a victim and i just couldnâ€™t risk that, that would have truly caused irreversible damage to me.  i know myself and i couldnâ€™t not have recovered from that. 
i knew that during questioning my own integrity would have been scrutinised.  how much alcohol i had drank? (2 glasses of champagne) what was i wearing? (trousers and a low cut top) even then i wouldnâ€™t have imagined my underwear would be considered relevant! 
this nonsense confirms to me that i made the right decision.  which is horrible.  it shouldnâ€™t be right for people to keep quiet! #thisisnotconsent

text:
over 2 years ago i went to a psychiatrist appointment with my girlfriend. it wasnâ€™t my first and i knew it wouldnâ€™t be my last as i had been under a mental health team for some years now but my mental health was spiralling out of control with the recent stress i had been under.
-
i left that appointment diagnosed and confused. i had never even heard of borderline personality disorder before. i didnâ€™t know what it meant and i was lost. i spent days googling i didnâ€™t sleep much at all trying to get my head around what bpd was. i printed off pages and pages of information to highlight because i just wanted answers.
-
at the beginning of the year i got diagnosed with ptsd and that was hard to understand. i was still scared and my body was still in shock after everything that had happened to me.
-
now iâ€™m thankful for the diagnosis because i understand myself more but this is one of the reasons i made perfectly_borderline because i wanted a safe space for anyone struggling with any mental health condition.
-
i want people to go on to instagram and see that they are not alone because i know how alone my mental health condition makes me feel.
-
i wanted to give people a real insight into what living with mental health conditions looks like.
this is my life, my family and my traumas and iâ€™m sharing them because i want to show you that you can love a â€œnormalâ€ life.
you can be in recovery and itâ€™s ok to struggle in recovery.
-
when you follow this instagram account you will always have somewhere to go and someone to talk to. i have big things planned for perfectly_borderline.
#perfectlyborderline

text:
today, i finished â€œwarriors donâ€™t cryâ€ and has reminded me of all of my battles that i have mostly overcome. a young 15 year-old fighting racism and bigotry. overcoming physical and emotional hardships only because she was black. each of us have our own stories, challenges, barriers that we are facing. memories that hold us back or push us forward. they say that â€œ35% of women globally have experienced physical or sexual assaultâ€ and â€œ120 million girls have experienced forced sex or other sexual actsâ€ (@unwomen). in the us, â€œevery 98 secondsâ€ someone is being sexually assaulted (@rainn). survivors of sexual assault are more likely to have ptsd,  anxiety, depression, thoughts of suicide, start to use drugs, in which are all after affects. i choose to find a picture of me that symbolized a time of vulnerability, purity, unconditional kindness and love. a time where my worries were about how to get my cousins to give me more candy without my parents knowing. a time where i had people showering me with kisses, love, smiles and hope. i choose these two pictures because there were no dark secrets or shame about my past/experiences. my four years of college, were a constant battle to raise awareness of sexual assault, violence that i felt the student body needed to be constantly reminded and for survivors to know they were not alone. today, i look at these pictures and remind myself that my sad experiences, that many other women and men have gone through, do not own us. we have the power to rewrite our own stories. to empower other survivors and to support each other. i share this today because my own memories that i wish i could erase are much clearer during this time of month. the past 3 years have gone by and i am still gathering my courage to fight my inner demons. 
if you are a victim of sexual assault go to www.rainn.org/get-help 
you are never aloneâ¤ï¸
â€¢
â€¢
â€¢
#overcomingfears #loveyourself #metoo

text:
#thisisnotconsent
an irish girl (17) was raped and the (female) lawyer of the perpetrator (27) pointed to girls lacy thong (which she wore under her clothes - for no one to see) in court some days ago - where df do we live? honestly, i'm in lack of word.
this poor young woman lived through a horrible event - she will never be able to forget what was done to her; the guy said it was consentual sex even though there were witnesses who saw him choking her, forcing himself onto her - and got away with it. (i really ask myself why they didn't help - but that is another point that triggers my rage).
let's get crystal clear: rapists rape, not clothes. read it over and over again if you don't understand it the first time. it makes me truly angry that rape culture is still a thing and that the victime is blamed for what is done to her. wasn't the event itself bad enough, do we really need to make it even worse for her by not believing her words?
even if someone stands buttnaked right in front of you, without consent, it's rape. you have no right to touch someone else (or even more), if there's no explicit consent.
no means no, stop means no, i'm not sure means no - the list is endless. the absence of consent is rape. point.

text:
my art installation #myfirstharassment will be presented in avignon city hall. the mayor's office invited me to show this project  in the context of international day for the elimination of violence against women. 
with #myfirstharassment i address the subject of harassment through the memory of women and their testimonies.
when harassment survivors finds the courage to speak up, theyâ€™re not believed or listened to. i wanted to be the listener. so iâ€™ve met women and i asked: â€œwhat is your first memory of harassment?â€, and i really listened, using alice millerâ€™s â€œenlightened witnessâ€ method to help women go further. i gathered their stories in visual and sound collages in an immersive installation, that reveals the power of building our own narrative as women.
if you are around avignon those days, come for the opening on the 26th at 5 pm. if you live too far, contact my agency @mtartagency to commission the show in your town ;)
many thanks to @villedavignon mayor @cecilehelle for inviting me showing this project, to johanna rage for organizing it and to @marinetanguyart for her support!
***

text:
there once was a little boy who had a bad temper. his father gave him a bag of nails and told him that every time he lost his temper, he must hammer a nail into the back of the fence. the first day the boy had driven 37 nails into the fence. over the next few weeks, as he learned to control his anger, the number of nails hammered daily gradually dwindled down. he discovered it was easier to hold his temper than to drive those nails into the fence.
finally the day came when the boy didnâ€™t lose his temper at all. he told his father about it and the father suggested that the boy now pull out one nail for each day that he was able to hold his temper. the days passed and the young boy was finally able to tell his father that all the nails were gone.
the father took his son by the hand and led him to the fence. he said, â€œyou have done well, my son, but look at the holes in the fence. the fence will never be the same. when you say things in anger, they leave a scar just like this one. you can put a knife in a man and draw it out. it wonâ€™t matter how many times you say iâ€™m sorry, the wound is still there.â€ a verbal wound is as bad as a physical one. 
friends are a very rare jewel, indeed. they make you smile and encourage you to succeed. they lend an ear, they share a word of praise, and they always want to open their hearts to us. #brandiva #thefence #abuse #metoo #women #coach #life #lifequotes #inspirationalquotes #inspiration #southafrica #lifecoach #verbalabuse #leadership #forgiveness #selfawareness #regret #shame #guilt

text:
tw - rape and suicide 
this is not consent . 
the 17 year old girl who's underwear was held up in court and used against her as an excuse for her rape  committed suicide earlier today, not believed, and humiliated . she said earlier this week that she felt like she'd been raped again during the two week 'trial' where it felt like she was being put on trial, more than her rapist was being put on trial. 
it desperately saddens me that over and over again in the 21st century what girls are wearing whilst they are raped is used against them, both by the perpetrators and by the court. 
rape is something that is still not always taken seriously and in a supposedly civilised society and this makes me feel ashamed of the uk. 
i ask you this - what sort of underwear should we, as women, be wearing in order to be taken seriously ? how many more women need to die before using her underwear against her is outlawed ?  even if i were to be wondering around naked, it would not mean i wanted to have sex and it wouldn't be an invite either .  why should what we choose to wear or what we don't choose to wear determine whether what has happened to us is valid, i mean babies are born naked and we don't think they are up for sex so why should anyone's lack of clothes determine what they are up to doing ?? it isn't right and it's time that the pinning people's rape on what they wear culture needs to stop. it is not an excuse. the clothes or lack of aren't what rapes people, the rapists are the ones who choose to rape . rape existed in the 19th century when women exposing their ankle was deemed to be improper and rape exists now . rape has always existed, regardless of the fashions of the time and unfortunately, it may always exist but we as a society need to start believing the victims and stop using and teaching our children invalid excuses for why rape is ok. rape is n e v e r ok and can never be justified, whether it is marital rape or not. rape is rape. â—¾
i'm sorry that this probably isn't a very well put together post but as i always say, i'd rather speak out about something i believe in than keep silent.
â—¾
#thisisnotconsent #nomeansno #metoo #blm #northernireland #feminism

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

text:
donâ€™t try and carry those who want to pull you down.
donâ€™t waste time trying to convince others of your worth and value. donâ€™t expend valuable energy minimizing you so that others feel more comfortable around you. 
a smaller you does not make a bigger them. 
donâ€™t try to hang on to those who have let go of you. 
donâ€™t be controlled by those who wonâ€™t allow you to thrive and flourish. make sure those closest to you are for you, talk to you, not about you, are not jealous of you, not threatened by you, not intimidated by you, not wanting to leverage you, and donâ€™t want to be you. you need them to be them and to bring out the best in you. those closest to you are the ones that truly have the capacity to hurt or heal. finding heaven in the midst of hormonal hell has a checklist and strategy to find your tribe!!

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr

text: when i had lost weight a year back, all my relatively were like your face has reduced a lot. you have lost the glow. your face is smaller as compared to the body. i used to get fed up explaining that there is no target weight loss. but someone had to say something or the other. it affected me and i once very decently told one of my relatives that i don't like them judging my body like that but they took it in a wrong, defensive way. it was one of the main reasons for me giving up exercising because not many people gave me a thumbs up.  but now, when i had put on weight, my face was plumply and i myself didn't like the way i looked, i didnt like the way i felt . not even one person came up to me and genuinely said that i had put on weight and i should reduce it because its not good for my health. when i saw this difference... i got to know that nobody really gives a damn. its just when you rise, other cant see you rising. on one side where my boyfriend was cheering me up for showing consistency and healthy eating. the other side my relatives discouraged me.  from that moment i realized i cannot make everyone happy but i can make myself happy and satisfied. and there is no need to impress others! so here i am, doing my bit. #impress #impressyourself #rise #riseabliveothers #weightloss #weightissues #weightlosstransformation ##satisfying #discouraged #stayfit #dowhatisright #fitnessmotivation #motivationalquotes #panchkuka #chandigarh #indianfoodie #metoo

#endsexualviolence #gof #greenolivefoundation.
thank you @warif_ng
@regran_ed from @warif_ng -  what happens to a rape survivor  when she seeks help on the streets?
.
.
abaad, a lebanese ngo, conducted a social experiment to see how bystanders would react.

an actress played the role of a rape survivor seeking help in public. these are the real reactions she got.
blaming the survivor is still very prevalent in our society todayâ€™, it could have happened anywhere and the reactions would still be the same. 
we need to do better as bystanders so that women and girls can live in a society free from rape and sexual violence.

text:
@regrann from @dr_with_a_good_handwriting -  marriage is not consent.
.
of all the victims, i am most unfortunate
i don't compare pain to pain
but my story is a tragedy
and my body is a bane
these bangles are shackles
this mangalsutra a noose
the sindoor is my branding mark
marriage was a ruse
i tried to complain, i tried to scream
but his hand was clasped on my mouth
i tried to explain, i tried to convince
but his other hand was under my saree
and that was the first time that he broke my soul
he does it over and over every night
i have given up, i oblige
more than his desires, it satisfies his ego
he invades me every time
bruises have replaced my jewellery
i am his favourite game
and i cannot help me
not the laws nor the in-laws
nor the parents neither the friends
they mocked me, told me to bear a child
and i can't help but wonder, are you all plotting against me?
how cruel must those be, 
who believe my body is made to please a man
"but he's your husband"- no, he's a monster
and i am a woman
to all of you out there: please do understand
my body is only mine
and marriage is not consent
he can't do it just because he can. Â©dr_with_a_good_handwriting

text:
tuesday, november 27th at the university of minnesota, in concert with a panel of nonprofit leaders from around the twin cities, the kelly nicole foundation proudly presents an unforgettable evening of music, film and inspiration.  join us for an artistic exploration of overcoming shame featuring music by the late artist, kelly nicole and the award-winning documentary on her battle with a trauma-based eating disorder.  inspired by the lyric "it's all my fault, but i'm not to blame," the panel will take audience questions, so we want to hear from you.  bring a friend and join the conversation.  free food, great music and film.  walter library 402, november 27th at 5:30pm.  visit kellynicole.com for more information on the music behind the mission.  admission will be free.  survivors will be heard.

#amplified #kellynicolefoundation #hatebecoming #ptsd #trauma #metoo #edrecovery #eatingdisorderawareness #music #film #art #mentalhealth #umn #universityofminnesota

text:
baiq nuril maqnun, seorang pegawai honorer di sman 7 mataram oleh mahkamah agung (ma) dinyatakan bersalah melakukan tindak pidana sebagaimana diatur dalam pasal 27 ayat (1) uu ite dan divonis enam bulan penjara serta kewajiban membayar denda sebesar rp 500 juta. secara sederhana nuril dianggap terbukti oleh ma telah melakukan penyebaran percakapan asusila kepala sekolah smu 7 mataram. padahal, sebelumnya pn mataram menyatakan ia tidak terbukti mentransmisikan konten yang bermuatan pelanggaran kesusilaan. dalam persidangan, majelis hakim pn mataram bahkan menyatakan bahwa unsur â€œtanpa hak mendistribusikan dan/atau mentransmisikan dan/atau membuat dapat diaksesnya informasi elektronik dana/atau dokumen elektronikâ€ tidak terbukti sebab bukan ia yang melakukan penyebaran tersebut, melainkan pihak lain.
sebelumnya ketika bertugas di sman 7 mataram, baiq nuril sering mendapatkan perlakuan pelecehan dari kepala sekolah sman 7 mataram. contoh, ia sering dihubungi oleh kepala sekolah sman 7 mataram dan harus mendengarkan yang bersangkutan menceritakan pengalamannya berhubungan seksual dengan wanita lain yang mana bukan istrinya sendiri. merasa tidak nyaman dengan hal tersebut dan untuk membuktikan bahwa dirinya tidak terlibat hubungan gelap seperti yang dibicarakan orang sekitarnya, baiq nuril pun merekam pembicaraannya. atas dasar ini kemudian kepala sekolah sman 7 mataram melaporkannya ke penegak hukum.
putusan ma ini memiliki catatan tersendiri yang harus dikritisi bersama. karena dalam lingkup peradilan, hakim ma terikat pada perma no. 3 tahun 2017 tentang pedoman mengadili perempuan yang berhadapan dengan hukum, termasuk dalam konteks perempuan yang didakwa melakukan tindak pidana. lewat pasal 3 perma tersebut hakim wajib mengindentifikasi situasi perlakuan tidak setara yang diterima perempuan yang berhadapan dengan hukum, hal ini jelas dialami oleh baiq nuril yang merupakan korban kekerasan seksual.
#saveibunuril #tolakeksekusibunuril #revisiuuite #stopkekerasanseksual #speakup #metoo

text:
this year, i'm thankful for my diabetes. this disease helped me find myself. it helped me heal my mind, body, and spirit.

photos left to right: summer 2017, before my diagnosis. november 2018, 13 months since diagnosis.

thank you, diabetes.

thank you for being the thing that finally reconnected me with my body after my assault. thank you for being the microphone for what my body had been screaming since that morning 12+ years ago. thank you for helping me put my trauma into perspective. thank you for teaching me how to care for myself, to nourish myself mentally, emotionally, physically, spiritually. thank you for giving me the courage to go into nature and face myself, my thoughts, my trauma. thank you for the changes you helped make in my physical and mental health that empowered me to walk across catalina island for a second time.  thank you for being the catalyst for so much positive change in my life. thank you for teaching me compassion for myself. thank you for giving me a framework to manage my health in a way that feels empowering vs discouraging; healthy vs obsessive; natural and intuitive versus violent and damaging.

also: one in three americans are pre-diabetic. one in three. please ask for a blood glucose test at your next doctor's appointment. this disease is political af. make no mistake, i did the work, and (not but) i recognize my privilege here. thankfully, i was gainfully employed with primo benefits when i was diagnosed. if i had to work 2-3 jobs and didn't have time to exercise, if i couldn't afford healthy fresh food, if i couldn't afford health insurance, if i had any additional stressor like kids or marriage issues, it would be near impossible to manage this disease as effectively as i was able to immediately following my diagnosis.

diabetes is my #everydayreality. i want this to be a conversation about how our bodies store and manifest trauma when we ignore our mental health. this disease is the best thing that ever happened to me because it liberated me. i want to talk about that.

also: one in three americans are pre-diabetic. one in three. please ask for a blood glucose test at your next doctor's appointment. this disease is political af. make no mistake, i did the work, and (not but) i recognize my privilege here. thankfully, i was gainfully employed with primo benefits when i was diagnosed. if i had to work 2-3 jobs and didn't have time to exercise, if i couldn't afford healthy fresh food, if i couldn't afford health insurance, if i had any additional stressor like kids or marriage issues, it would be near impossible to manage this disease as effectively as i was able to immediately following my diagnosis.

diabetes is my  i want this to be a conversation about how our bodies store and manifest trauma when we ignore our mental health. this disease is the best thing that ever happened to me because it liberated me. i want to talk about that.

text:
tuesday, november 27th at the university of minnesota, in concert with a panel of nonprofit leaders from around the twin cities, the kelly nicole foundation proudly presents an unforgettable evening of music, film and inspiration.  join us for an artistic exploration of overcoming shame featuring music by the late artist, kelly nicole and the award-winning documentary on her battle with a trauma-based eating disorder.  inspired by the lyric "it's all my fault, but i'm not to blame," the panel will take audience questions, so we want to hear from you.  bring a friend and join the conversation.  free food, great music and film.  walter library 402, november 27th at 5:30pm.  visit kellynicole.com for more information on the music behind the mission.  admission will be free.  survivors will be heard.

text:
tuesday, november 27th at the university of minnesota, in concert with a panel of nonprofit leaders from around the twin cities, the kelly nicole foundation proudly presents an unforgettable evening of music, film and inspiration.  join us for an artistic exploration of overcoming shame featuring music by the late artist, kelly nicole and the award-winning documentary on her battle with a trauma-based eating disorder.  inspired by the lyric "it's all my fault, but i'm not to blame," the panel will take audience questions, so we want to hear from you.  bring a friend and join the conversation.  free food, great music and film.  walter library 402, november 27th at 5:30pm.  visit kellynicole.com for more information on the music behind the mission.  admission will be free.  survivors will be heard.

#amplified #kellynicolefoundation #hatebecoming #ptsd #trauma #metoo #edrecovery #eatingdisorderawareness #music #film #art #mentalhealth #umn #universityofminnesota

text:
good morning peeps, pop pop needs to get serious today. i was and still am freaked out that one of our family members was sexually assaulted. thank goodness it did not happen at our event, however the perpetrator showed up at our party last week. he is no longer welcome. i am posting what my @deserthearts family posted before this years festival.  read this & take it to heart.  hello family, we'd like to get serious for a moment... recent reports from the festival community about rampant sexual harassment at other festivals have given us pause. 
we're saddened that this kind of behavior is still prevalent and want to give a very firm reminder before we gather together soon:

desert hearts has an absolute *zero tolerance policy* for any form of harassment. as a community, it is our responsibility to care for one another and to ensure we are maintaining a safe container for all forms of healthy self expression.

please remember to ask first - and wait for their consent - before touching others. there are a lot of things that do not imply consent. sexy costumes are not consent, nudity is not consent, accepting a gift is not consent, being drunk is not consent, being asleep is not consent, and being too scared to resist is not consent.

consent is an agreement between people that are properly informed, are not under coercion, and are not incapacitated. consent is when both parties clearly and openly communicate with one another that they agree to future actions.

if you or someone you know are experiencing harassment at the event, please reach out to a member of our safety team.

and most importantly, remember that we are the change we wish to see in the world about how to be loving, kind, and respectful to one another. it starts first with you, with us, to create a larger change in the festival community and the world we share with one another. 
house, techno, and loveâ€¦ we are all desert heartsğŸ’—  thanks for reading we all need to care of each other!! if you ever are made to feel uncomfortable, speak up!! i â¤ï¸yâ€™all letâ€™s keep our community safe for everyone.  predators stay away !! #nomeansno #metoo #vibevessel #love #plur #consent #askfirst

#neverokay #saveibunuril

text:
@regrann from @adivergentpoet -  for @shespeaksforthechange #qotd
2 people. one forces (physically, behaviourally or emotionally) the other to have sex. what do you call it? rape, right?
only, if they were married, what difference would it make?
itâ€™s still non-consensual. itâ€™s still unwanted by one. itâ€™s still rape. albeit, marital rape.
when you marry, you donâ€™t sign a contract saying â€œmy partner owns my body & can use it as he/she deems â€˜usefulâ€™ â€œ; then where does â€˜obligationâ€™ come up from? is marrying someone a favour done to them, or a loan that they have pay back with their body?
then why speak of marriage & sex in the same breathe? the act of marrying only builds the foundation of a relationship which is further strengthened by respect & trust; then love (maybe) & then only do carnal indulgences find a place, ideally.
i wonder what those â€˜marriedâ€™ people think when they force themselves upon their partners; that marriage gives them the â€˜right to have sexâ€™? sex without consent is rape; hence a criminal offence; & what, marrying sanctifies it??? tsk tsk.
law? yes there should be; but wait a secâ€¦ isnâ€™t there a law against dowry? tell me, how many incidences are reported? & how many of them are false? now take marital rapeâ€¦how many people will file a case against their own spouse? (considering that familyâ€™s izzat/honor comes first rather than a memberâ€™s dignity, many-a-times)
all in all, this is a debate that should have a definite end (that no sex isnâ€™t an obligation in marriage; yes, marital rape is rape; yes, there should be a law against it).
but, as i like to think of life in general, thereâ€™s not much that is black or white; most of it is gray, in a million different shades; & so is this topic; else it wonâ€™t be debate-ed, would it be?

thanks for your patience & time. hope you agree with this foalâ€™s whining. feel free to comment.
(all those questions have very simple, obvious answers, by my own intelligence (which is very low)â€¦hence left as rhetoric. apologies if itâ€™s annoying.) #arnabdeykhan #shespeaksforthechange #strongwomenquotes #strongwomen #shespeakstruth #metooindia #metoo #yesindeed #yesforyes #herstory #proudtobeawoman #girlpower

text:
#16dayactivism atau 16 hari anti kekerasan terhadap perempuan diperingati setiap tahunnya sebagai strategi untuk mengajak setiap orang terlibat aktif dalam upaya penghapusan segala bentuk kekerasan terhadap perempuan. .
.
25 november dipilih sebagai hari yang mengawali untuk menghormati perjuangan mirabal bersaudara (patria, minerva dan maria teresa) yang tak henti memperjuangkan demokrasi dan keadilan, serta menjadi simbol perlawanan kediktatoran penguasa republik dominika pada waktu itu. .
.
ingin terlibat dalam peringatan #16dayactivism tahun ini..? .
.
kosongkan jadwal mu ya di selasa, 27 november 2018 nanti. .
.
perempuan mahardhika bakal bikin acara menarik di gedung lbh jakarta yang membuat kamu dan teman2 bisa ambil bagian untuk menghapus segala bentuk kekerasan terhadap perempuan. 
#akhirisekarang
#mudamelawan 
#metoo 
#endviolence
#zerotolerance 
#genderviolence 
#16haktp

text:
***full poem in bio***
unspoken.

he called
the woman 
he claimed
to love,
his 'bitch'
and i
watched as
a part of 
her was
stripped away,

watched as
her desolate 
eyes filled
with delusional
images of 
his kindness -
blinking no
more than 
once so 
as to never
consolidate 
a life 
without him.

i watched 
a man
call his lover
a 'slut' today.
felt his 
words as 
clean and
sharp as a blade,

and i saw 
the blood
before i felt
its pain,
heard her cry
before 
she felt 
his words 
i winced, as
she wore
femininity 
just for him,
while he 
wore fangs
for a heart

he only craved 
the taste of 
metallic lust.
his gaze
was all
consuming,
and she never
stopped feeding
him.

but still
i cried
in shock
the day
a man struck me.

the way his
blow aimed to
convince me,
of just how
disposable 
i am,

how easily 
his love could
turn to fire,
and i
remember
learning how
smoke 
inhalation kills
faster than the 
burn.

and i breathed 
him in with
bated breath
and this time,
i felt the pain
before it came
to life on 
my skin.

carried 
his warmth
in all my 
nerves, and

each day

my cells
still routinely
place him
inside each 
regenerated 
atom

and i
still harvest
his scent 
in my lungs -

some wildfires 
cannot be 
tamed
and maybe,

i'm the 
unidentified 
casualty in
my own skin.

text:
tuesday, november 27th at the university of minnesota, in concert with a panel of nonprofit leaders from around the twin cities, the kelly nicole foundation proudly presents an unforgettable evening of music, film and inspiration.  join us for an artistic exploration of overcoming shame featuring music by the late artist, kelly nicole and the award-winning documentary on her battle with a trauma-based eating disorder.  inspired by the lyric "it's all my fault, but i'm not to blame," the panel will take audience questions, so we want to hear from you.  bring a friend and join the conversation.  free food, great music and film.  walter library 402, november 27th at 5:30pm.  visit kellynicole.com for more information on the music behind the mission.  admission will be free.  survivors will be heard.

#amplified #kellynicolefoundation #hatebecoming #ptsd #trauma #metoo #edrecovery #eatingdisorderawareness #music #film #art #mentalhealth #umn #universityofminnesota

text:
.
the shanghai series 
#2
.
neighbourhoods are often sharply defined in shanghai
.
the riverside bund was always unique, and the other early settlements, old town and the foreign concessions, both had walls and were self-governed, so they developed their own street layouts and building styles
.
these boundaries remain obvious, and often the simple act of crossing a street is like entering another country or another era
.
this building is right across the bund promenade and looks nothing chinese to say the least!
.

one of the qualities that make us sentient is the society we have built and the web of relationships we are a part of. we try to find balance in ourselves and in our relationships. 
moments of bliss, clarity and togetherness punctuated by moments of struggle and confusion, we are all essentially tied up together.

text:
breaking down stereotypes, raising prejudice-free children: @celinedion launches @celinununu a gender-neutral collection of children's clothing with a hope to â€œencourage a dialogue of equality and possibility.â€ @metheotherfilm hopes to raise awareness of our oneness as a human race by telling stories that defy perceived stereotypes, but honor the nobility of the human soul.

#celiondion #celinununu #diversity #prejudice #otherness #oneness #metheother #gender #stereotypes #huffingtonpost @huffpost @curtismwong  me, the "other" - a film celebrating diversity through stories of 12 students in michigan. their journeys through adversity and prejudice will open hearts to the humanity within all of us. the diverse group ranges from an african-american acting student from flint who tells a personal heartbreaking story of the current water crisis in her community; a student from mexico on the daca program living in fear of deportation; a pakistani muslim immigrant; an interracial married couple; a #metoo story of an orphaned baha'i immigrant from cameroon; a gay christian couple living with chronic lyme disease and aspergers; and a 66-year-old transgendered student who was homeless and alcohol and drug-dependent but chose education over suicide.

text:
last night i got to share my heart and soul for my first art exhibition. seeing my work hung on the walls along other artists was surreal. hearing the comments, seeing people take pictures, and discuss the works was so scary, until i heard what they were saying. they got it. they get it. they felt every brush stroke along with me. then to have quite a few people make it a point to find me, and ask about the work. to discuss the feeling and meaning. to hear that my work moved people... i canâ€™t even express the joy (not happiness, there is a difference) that i felt. it was overwhelming to the point of tears. i was so moved to know my pain and healing was turned into something beautiful that stirred people deep inside. my work provoked feelings, thoughts, discussions. last night i found my purpose. last night then going out with my friends to celebrate, i looked at us all on the dance floor, dancing ridiculous to bell biv devoe, and had to hold back happy tears. horrible circumstances brought me back to texas. i was so angry for so long, and could not understand why. and though i still have plans of leaving, i know i landed right where i needed. iâ€™m where i need to be for now. my tribe has grown and filled with loving artists, dreamers and musicians. for now. these people, (not the location where i am) they are my â€œhome.â€
.

.

text:
enam belas fest kembali lagi !!
.
.
.

saya perempuan,saya generasi milenial.dimana zaman yang sudah modern namun beberapa pemikiran masih zaman dahulu.masih banyak masyarakat yang belum paham betul dengan kesetaraan gender.yang menyebabkan korbannya adalah perempuan. diam,itulah salah satu cara untuk melindungi dirinya.dusta,itulah yang disimpan dalam dirinya.
inilah saatnya kita mendengarkan mereka.menghargai mereka.mereka yang sudah berusaha bangkit,namun dijatuhkan kembali.saya mendukung kampanye penghapusan kekerasan berbasis gender dan seksualitas ini.
16 hari melihat
16 hari mendengar
16 hari curhat
16 hari cari solusi
16 hari tanpa kekerasan â¡16 film festival bali merupakan festival film untuk memperingati kampanye 16 hari anti kekerasan terhadap perempuan (16 days of activism against gender violence) diadakan selama 16 hari.25 november-10 desember 2018

text:
i'm going to be okay. this is what i tell myself all the time. i mean one day it has to get better, right?
i wrote this poem at the beginning of october, in the middle of the night right after having a nightmare. i don't know why i wrote this. i don't even like it but i decided to share it on here anyway. because it might help someone who feels just like me. i know it's hard, it's so damn hard to think positive sometimes. especially right now, when my mental illness ruins my physical health.
but then i think about all the positive things that happened this year: my weightloss, opening up to friends about my past and my mental illness, seeing my friends again after a year apart, getting a cat, getting an open ended contract at work,...
i would be lying if i told you i'm okay and at peace with my past. but it's better than last year so i'm slowly getting better. and this is what's important.
.
.

text:
so far one this is one of the best quotes i've ever heard
more important than the act of abuse, is to acknowledge the trauma
in this context, 9 out of 10 abused children don't get a chance to speak up for the fear of threatening
in their brain there is no difference between reality and imagination
they can't distinguish them so they feel the words that torture the same way they go through the physical pain
over-burdening a child with the responsibility of taking the pain and shutting it down, drains the childhood out of them
they become the most raging adults who have no roots
like a building with weak basement
living the childhood properly with unconditional love empowers the future
well raised children are the strongest ones
whether as those who do not heal, are affected and drowned by every simple issue

let me be honest,
do you want a porn actor/actress generation or drug addict left behind?
or successful happy and healthy people living in the world
next time, a hand is raised to bring down the value of every child
make it stop
heal yourself, heal the world;
transform the cosmos!
and if you are victim, or know them
raise your hand to say goodbye and break the chain of the abusive cycle
and if you like, share your story
i'm sincerely proud of those who rise every single time
those who fight against the planned torture of psychological war;
on the soft delicate skin of our purest ones; children ğŸ™

love
- zahra

yes, i am posting again. and without a watermark. i thought about it and decided that i will assert my copyright in the text. i cannot imagine how this is unclear but this is my account in my real name. its a picture of me wearing a saree i bought. my husband is the photographer. it was taken in our bedroom because i was too lazy to stand up to shoot this saree. i am not a model or an influencer or any kind of celebrity. just a working mother and wife who loves sarees, jewelry and lipstick. instagram is where i come to play dress up. itâ€™s a break from the rest of my rather brain intensive work. .

the saree is a lovely black jamdani from @weavestory_mr who does not pay me to tag them. the necklace is a gift from my stepdaughter who bought it from a friend who makes jewelry @johanne.mohr i am not paid to say this but i do think that the necklace is gorgeous and went beautifully with this saree! you should definitely check out her beautiful pieces. .

i am not on instagram commercially. i do this for fun and to catalogue my growing collection of sarees. sarees that each have a story. feel free to enjoy them or unfollow. but please donâ€™t use my photos without my consent.âš ï¸ . 
it should go without saying that that it is unethical to use my or anyoneâ€™s picture without their consent & i will call it out. i simply will not be bullied out of the playground. .

other things that should go without saying:
âi will not marry you or date you or meetup with you (see note above about husband). use one of the many dating apps dude. insta is not one.
âi will delete & block anyone who makes inappropriate comments that include any part of my anatomy. nothing to do with #metoo itâ€™s simple decency.
and finally,
âœ…i own my images on this wall. donâ€™t steal them. .

text:
thanks so much @alannahale for this amazing capture of @suzanne_barr_food and i.

this summer we spent a crazy , wild, growth filled summer in pec. i have to admit, iâ€™m pretty grateful for this opportunity. before pec i was in the darkest of spaces in my life. i was using a lot of substances and felt really lost dazed and confused. i was so glad to be thrust into an environment that shook up my world. i think this may have saved my life, again. thanks stove. 
this summer i got a chance to experience racism + sexism for what felt like the first time in my life. this really changed me. itâ€™s shifted my entire paradigm about the #metoo movement and , yes, sometimes people do lie. men and women. 
i got a chance to reconnect with some of my favourite people on the planet @suzanne_barr_food @mohammad_khoda @flamingoals. 
i also got a chance to experience what itâ€™s like to work for great people with their intentions in all the right places. sometimes survival mode overtakes great instincts , and that gets murky really quickly. itâ€™s not easy running a business, iâ€™ve learnt and iâ€™ve heard. 
1) take a risk. leap and trust faith! all things will move me forward into greater blessings.
2)know your worth! people will often attempt to tell you what you deserve. let them know what the truth actually is.
3)watch your mouth. people are easy to trust, but! people are also motherfuckers. always test the waters with one toe.
4) be kind and forgiving. we are all going through this crazy human experience. love is the key to all healing of the soul.
5) know when to walk away. there is a point when you just have to say â€œno.â€ that is ok, too.

whatever you are going through, know that there is help and support available all around. there are people, spaces and graces that will bring you to new waters and higher heights than youâ€™ve ever imagined ğŸ¦‹

text: for my final speech in my public speaking class, i had to give a 6-8 minute persuasive speech on something i felt strongly about and provide credibility and evidence to back it up. i took this opportunity to tell my story to a classroom full of students who don't really know me or my life; and i am so glad that i did. despite suffering through a minor panic attack during my entire speech, i managed to make the impact that i wanted and got a perfect score on my speech. i had a classmate record it for me and if you would like to see it, dm me and i can email you a link to it. i am sure a lot of you will scroll past and not care, and that's fine. but if you are even slightly interested in hearing my story and hearing why i believe the justice system is failing sexual assault survivors, dm me, it's only 7 and a half minutes long. and maybe you will understand me a little better. #metoo #survivor

text:
thanks so much @alannahale for this amazing capture of @suzanne_barr_food and i.

this summer we spent a crazy , wild, growth filled summer in pec. i have to admit, iâ€™m pretty grateful for this opportunity. before pec i was in the darkest of spaces in my life. i was using a lot of substances and felt really lost dazed and confused. i was so glad to be thrust into an environment that shook up my world. i think this may have saved my life, again. thanks stove. 
this summer i got a chance to experience racism + sexism for what felt like the first time in my life. this really changed me. itâ€™s shifted my entire paradigm about the #metoo movement and , yes, sometimes people do lie. men and women. 
i got a chance to reconnect with some of my favourite people on the planet @suzanne_barr_food @mohammad_khoda @flamingoals. 
i also got a chance to experience what itâ€™s like to work for great people with their intentions in all the right places. sometimes survival mode overtakes great instincts , and that gets murky really quickly. itâ€™s not easy running a business, iâ€™ve learnt and iâ€™ve heard. 
1) take a risk. leap and trust faith! all things will move me forward into greater blessings.
2)know your worth! people will often attempt to tell you what you deserve. let them know what the truth actually is.
3)watch your mouth. people are easy to trust, but! people are also motherfuckers. always test the waters with one toe.
4) be kind and forgiving. we are all going through this crazy human experience. love is the key to all healing of the soul.
5) know when to walk away. there is a point when you just have to say â€œno.â€ that is ok, too.

whatever you are going through, know that there is help and support available all around. there are people, spaces and graces that will bring you to new waters and higher heights than youâ€™ve ever imagined ğŸ¦‹

text:
make #justiceforrajalakshmi go viral.

source: counterview @dbrinelle brinelle d'souza, who is with the centre for health and mental health, school of social work, tata institute of social sciences, mumbai, has prepared a strong statement to protest the brutal murder of 13-year-old rajalakshmi.
she demands that:
â€¢the government of tamil nadu provides the victimâ€™s family protection in the wake of caste tensions and hostilities that may arise as a fall out of the brutal murder. without proper protection, the family may flee the village in the face of threats and harassment from the accused and others in the village as is often the case.
â€¢the government of tamil nadu provide the family the legal and financial support to fight the case till the cause of justice is served.
â€¢the government of tamil nadu arranges for necessary counselling and psychosocial services for the family to deal with their deep personal loss and trauma.

text:
what was the most important advice you gave been given as a survivor of sexual violence?
â¡ï¸ swipe to read about mine â¡ï¸
trust that when silence presents itself as a tempting prospect
you will be wise enough to tell your story
trust that when the weight of your trauma pulls you under
you will be wise enough to know where the surface is
trust that when you have no control 
you will be wise enough to not blame yourself
trust that when you feel trapped again
you will be wise enough to know that being trapped provides an opportunity to find yourself.
trust that when you panic and cry and ask if you will be okay 
you will be wise enough. 
trust the process.
â¡ï¸â¡ï¸â¡ï¸
"trust the process." when i was first given such advice after i was sexually assaulted, i tried desperately to figure out what exactly that meant. moreso since it was coming from a very influential and healing person in my life, a person who has quite literally saved my life, my therapist. for a while i started to think my therapist herself was "the process," as when i went to her in moments of crisis and trusted her with my most vulnerable thoughts i always left feeling better without even noticing my gradual return to calmness over the source of our session.
.
.
.

#repost @bruthawitsoul
â€¢ â€¢ â€¢ â€¢ â€¢
actor #terrycrews just testified before the senate judiciary committee on sexual assault legislation known as the survivor's bill of rights.
-
"i am honored to use my platform and story to help create additional civil rights protections for #survivors across the nation under the sexual assault survivors bill of rights," crews said.
-
crews shared his experience with sexual #assault on twitter last year, revealing that a high-level hollywood executive groped him.
-
crews's testimony brought several in the hearing to tears. he said his first though to being sexually assaulted at a party in front of his wife was to respond with #violence .
-
"senator, as a black man in america," crews said, "you only have a few shots at success. you only have a few chances to make yourself a valuable part of the community."
-
crews recounted leaving the party and reporting the incident to senior executives at the agency of the man who assaulted him â€” asking them, what they planned to do about the " #predator you have roaming the hallways."
-
"i said 'this is unacceptable,"
-
"then nothing happened," he told the panel.
-
"the culture of the time, i believed that nobody would believe me if i went public," he said.
-
crews credited #metoo with changing the power dynamics in hollywood and countless other industries.
-
"the me too movement empowered me to tell my story,"
-
crews blamed what he called a "cult of masculinity" in #hollywood .
-
"this behavior is expected as part of the job, this #harassment, abuse, even #rape , is part of your job description," he said. "what's happened to me, has happened to many, many other men."
-
crews also revealed in testimony on that he will not be in "the expendables 4" because he didnâ€™t drop the case and the same producer is "under his own sexual assault investigation, and abusers protect abusers."
-
"when you look at the culture with men not holding other men accountable, it turns into something that no one wants: a community that totally looks the other way while men, women, children are being raped," crews said.

#standup #stereotypes #50cent #weareallhuman #dumptrump #empowerment  #womenempowerment #moviest

text:
hi everyone!  i'm ash of ashley kaplan photography.  my real name is ashley, but i prefer ash as most people i've met in my adult life call me this.  i chose my business name using my full name just because i thought it sounded better :-) ! 
i am a hybrid lifestyle-documentary photographer capturing family love stories.  i love photographing adventurous families, emotive connections, the small details, beautiful places, and the authentic moments that make each family unique.  in a sentence, my business is love and i create artistic heirlooms <3 
thank you for being here!  1,000 more of you that have decided to follow along here -thank you! - since last time i did a proper introduction. i'd love for you to comment below and tell me who you are, where you are, and something special to know about you!

if you've followed my instagram stories for a while, you know that i am political and way left of center.  i do love a good dialogue with folks that have radically different beliefs as mine... i was a philosophy minor in college so understanding why we think and believe what we do is something that fascinates me.  i can agree to disagree so long as we aren't debating human rights.  i''m pretty inflexible in my thinking about #humanrights because i believe in human dignity and:

#familiesbelongtogether and #nohumanbeingisillegal babies shouldn't be separated from their parents, no matter how they arrive to a country 
#blacklivesmatter and i believe that we need to reconcile and at least begin to discuss the genocide and slavery that our country was founded upon as we still see it playing out in the racist, nativist and disgusting dialogue that is being spewed by the orange monster in charge and the bubbling of white supremacy that has in truth always existed in this country (but i liked it way better when being a racist was still considered socially unacceptable). #metoo i also believe the women in the #metoo movement and think it is time for women to be in power because, well,  i think we'll do a better job! guys have had a long run at ruling the world, and it is just our time because #fuckpatriarchy 
these are some of my #truths and i'd love to learn more about you!

panawayâ€™s number one use is for muscle relief. if you work out, do hard labor picking up kids all day counts!, or slept funny this oils is amazing! my husband works hvac and this oil is what made him a believer! i rub this on his shoulders and back every night with copaiba to enhance the relief of a hard days work. if you like to use muscle soaks add a few drops to epsom salts to add to your bath! 
diffuse when you need a pick me up! pair it with stress away for our beloved root beer float blend! the kiddos love it!

text:
they say it takes a village and oooooh they were not kidding. we have so many people to thank for making last night a big success: - @salgadofenwick and @yegbuffalocafe for allowing us to use your beautiful space for the event and also for working during it! - @lindseycatherinephoto for not only buying a ticket but then also taking the best photos at the event.
- @kadydane for covering femme fÃªte on instagram and twitter in the moment, and @kadenavecomms for sponsoring portions of the event.
- @anothernisha for her powerful spoken word poetry.
- @alecia.vogel for making us all laugh and think differently about walruses.
- @smithstinecopper for donating 2 gorgeous necklaces for our door prizes, including a custom femme cabal themed "f" necklace.
- @kassieandsofia for donating 2 friendship necklaces for door prizes.
- @kellyspub104 for donating a gift card for a door prize and for being so accommodating as our after party location.
- cosmos on 124th for the delicious greek food
- @thecakesluts for the hilarious cakes and cupcakes

and of course, thank you to the cabal. we are so grateful to those of you who bought tickets, told your friends, showed up, had a good time, and hopefully left feeling some passion for this wonderful little community we are trying to build. 
so much love & gratitude. xo

text:
yep it's getting that time of year again, only 8 sleeps till we have a big 7 year old, and 38 more sleeps until christmas. i use to hate christmas with a passion, i was always the grinch, but since having my daughter i have tried my hardest to make it a special time of year for her. but now i'm all for christmas tree decorating in november, and blasting those carols, as this year i'm really excited to share this special time of year with tara and with my family. this year however with tara i am very aware of her needs and i won't be pressuring her to go see santa, or to go to the parades as i know she doesn't cope well with these, however i will push her out of her comfort zone a little, and we will be attending the special children's christmas party at mystery creek, so she can have some experiences i know she will enjoy. here's to a very special christmas this year.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

in the beginning,
my story not yours

where did my leg go ? have you seen my leg ? i had it just yesterday, i know i did, what happened, was i bad? i donâ€™t think so. no, i know i wasnâ€™t , come on , itâ€™s time to come home. 
i think iâ€™ll go to bed now, please god bring it back tonite so when i wake up it will be home again, home again, jiggity jig.

nope , itâ€™s not here.

i was four years old when my leg was amputated. no one bothered to tell me what was going to happen. and it never came back.

please hold me. someone tell me it will be ok. .
.

text:
so often we hear the term "domestic violence" and we automatically think of a guy beating a girl.
.
.
fact: there are also boys who are abused by girls, and most of the time the abuse goes on for a prolonged period of time, because:
.

1 - the boy refuses to fight back because she's a girl.
.

2 - the boy is too embarrassed to admit that a girl is abusing him.
.

3 - the boys think nobody will believe them.
.

people are people, and abusive behavior does not discriminate based on gender. so for all the guys reading this, please know that we are here for you too! nobody deserves to be abused by someone they love. ğŸ’¯
.
.

text: in addition to this amazing mural that couldnâ€™t ignored, i enjoyed this dope event today at the mosaic literary conference where the theme was the #metoo movement from a black and brown womanâ€™s perspective through literature/poetry/art...the shared stories through voice and print were heavy/eye opening yet motivating enough that they should be heard in a safe setting, people should be supported and support each other and able to heal, but we also need to include our men in these conversations because they too need to be heard, healed, and be an ally. women empowerment and the me too movement  doesnâ€™t equate to the absence or neglect of men, we need you in this movement too. essentially, women should be safe to feel and be comfortable in our own skin, unapologetically, not only when sharing stories of trauma, or on the healing journey, but in general, and not be automatically characterized as aggressive when itâ€™s simply just our organically made confidence. #mlc2018 #literaryfreedomproject #bronxmuseum #womenofcolor #womenempowerment #womenwriters #movitation

text:
i went to my deposition yesterday that the monster had ordered his lawyer to do for custody of the girls..... i stood my ground. i told the truth. i opened pandoras box. my best friend, he once asked me if i should go after the monster for more child support i replied no it wouldnt be a good idea, i said it would be like opening pandoras box. .
.
well he did. i did. the drugs. the abuse. the abandonment. the con to get back in the door. the stuff i never told anyone is now on record for the courts under oath as my whole truth. after 2 hours and 22 mins i finally broke a started to cry after the lawyer started victim shaming as the only way to get to me. i'm proud of myself for how i handled it. but i do wish it was all over.
.
.
.
#whyididntreport #btsadv #dvawareness #dv #teenabuse #metoo #rapeculture #victimshaming #breakthesilence #aclanofunicorns #iwillprevail #iamthestorm #pandorasbox

text:
we are extremely proud to announce our first â€œfearless familyâ€ production: "legally blonde: the musical.â€ this will serve as our transition musical from our season of defiance volume 1: upheaval into our volume 2 season (soon to be announced.) every role in this show was precast using our fearless family (and a few new faces) in order to highlight the dedication of our actors/techs/production team and to give them all the platform to use their voice.

we at fearless are always striving to create a safe space. a space where everyone can be who they are without fear of judgement or harassment.

in the current climate of the #timesup and #metoo movements, this show smashes through all time barriers to tackle such topics as gender bias, sexual harassment, and sexual assualt. this is not just something that is happening in hollywood. it is happening all around us, even within our own theatre community, and more often than not it has become a place where inappropriate behavior is shrugged off as if nothing more can be done. 
we at fearless are saying #timesup to those who abuse their power in our community. all spaces should be safe. this behavior can not be ignored.

we are professionals. we are artists. we are human. 
we learn, we grow, and we never stop fighting.

your voice matters. your art matters. we believe you. we believe in you. we stand with you.

we are survivors. we are fighters. we are fearless.

#befearless #notinourhouse #drivenashell #chiponourshoulder  #legallyblonde #timesup #legallyblondethemusical #nogoodtheatrekids #denver #colorado #theatre

the following words are from my work on calculating for #reparations. you can find a video on youtube with that name. 
#farts, by the way, are essential body functions, not #weapons of war. perhaps iâ€™m wrong when it comes to #darts, which iâ€™ve only played when drinking or drunk. asÃ­ es: #vinotinto. 
on this iâ€™m right: #dumptrump #decolonize (see the #colon there? decolonization is political #wastemanagement called #elimination of #toxins and #parasites. ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©ğŸ’©
in this short article, i give a few tips on how to calculate for the #human, #economic, and #environmental costs of police violence as we work towards decolonization on a world scale.

first, there is no one method or formula for determining reparations.

so much of the violence we experience is personalized. the violence we experience as individuals is always shared by other people and communities, yet how it affects us is embodied and related to who we are in this #earth walk. that's why this method was designed for people like you and #metoo.

second, calculating reparations is always an economic and #spiritual practice.

above all, the spiritual dimension of this method is central, and #survivors must lead each initiative. the point is to foster #healing, not pay for therapy and legal costs, and give people the support we require to create #solutions for ourselves and our beloved communities. so, what does healing mean for you as a #survivor of the violence you seek to stop? given your daily life and needs at this time, what do you need to put in place to learn and apply the method?

from a purely economic perspective, what aspects of healing can financial reparations facilitate? this question is the most direct, but it isn't as simple as it #sounds. #toot. #fart. for example, you might desire therapy and know that therapists cost a rate of, say $60-250 an hour in your town. what if no therapist in your local beloved community speaks your mother language of #flatulence and that's the language in which you #sense and #scent the world? what is the honest price tag for your therapy sessions if you have to travel three hours to see a therapist who shares your cultural #perspective? #poop.

text:
how do you talk to your preschoolers about consent, and bodily autonomy... if at all? when did you start introducing the concepts of body privacy alongside, perhaps, body positivity? or if you haven't, what are your thoughts and will it be something you approach one day? are you a family who proudly bares all at home, or are the bathroom doors locked for good reason? do you think that these topics need to be approached differently with boys and girls? and by whom? what are your memories of being educated in these matters during your own childhood? were you? ğŸ‘ªğŸ‘ªğŸ‘ª
.
 i'm half way through writing a blog post about how i personally approach the subjects of consent, bodily autonomy, body positivity and, to a degree, physical abuse (the risk of) with my children - but i'm so interested to hear what other families are doing/talking about and why. please share your thoughts below i'd really love to hear your unique view.
ğŸ‘ªğŸ‘ªğŸ‘ª
.
whilst i'm at it, i really recommend this light, scare-free and positive book about how to respect your body, and make sure others respect it too. its perfect to begin reading with preschoolers, and a good starting point if you're not sure about how to start talking to your children about consent and other similar topics. .
.
.
